# Optional dedicated speedtest backend for accurate, Ookla-comparable results.
# See server/speedtest-server.js for a reference implementation; deploy it
# close to your users. The server must expose CORS-enabled endpoints:
#   GET  /download?bytes=N   -> streams N incompressible bytes
#   POST /upload             -> accepts and discards a binary body
#   GET  /ping               -> responds immediately
#
# When unset, the test runs in browser-only mode against public endpoints and
# results are marked "Browser Estimate" / "Estimated results only".
# NOTE: NEXT_PUBLIC_* vars are inlined at build time — rebuild after changing.
NEXT_PUBLIC_TEST_SERVER_URL=
